##Create individual columns for Year, Month, and Day from Start.Time
ny$Trip.Year<- year(ny$Start.Time)
ny$Trip.Month<- month(ny$Start.Time)
ny$Trip.Day<- day(ny$Start.Time)
ny$Trip.Hour<- hour(ny$Start.Time)
ny$Trip.DOW<- weekdays(as.Date(ny$Start.Time))
ny$Trip.DurationMin<-ny$Trip.Duration/60

ch$Trip.Year<- year(ch$Start.Time)
ch$Trip.Month<- month(ch$Start.Time)
ch$Trip.Day<- day(ch$Start.Time)
ch$Trip.Hour<- hour(ch$Start.Time)
ch$Trip.DOW<- weekdays(as.Date(ch$Start.Time))
ch$Trip.DurationMin<-ch$Trip.Duration/60

wa$Trip.Year<- year(wa$Start.Time)
wa$Trip.Month<- month(wa$Start.Time)
wa$Trip.Day<- day(wa$Start.Time)
wa$Trip.Hour<- hour(wa$Start.Time)
wa$Trip.DOW<- weekdays(as.Date(wa$Start.Time))
wa$Trip.DurationMin<-wa$Trip.Duration/60

##Initial plot of data for exploration
##Plot of NY data
ggplot(aes(x = Trip.Day), data = ny) + geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'blue', binwidth = 0.5) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:31) + 
  ggtitle("Bikeshare Rides on Each Day of the Month - New York") + xlab("Day of Month") + ylab("Number of Trips")

##Plot of Chicago data
ggplot(aes(x = Trip.Day), data = ch) + geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'green', binwidth = 0.5) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:31) + 
  ggtitle("Bikeshare Rides on Each Day of the Month - Chicago") + xlab("Day of Month") + ylab("Number of Trips")

##Plot of Washington data
ggplot(aes(x = Trip.Day), data = wa) + geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'red', binwidth = 0.5) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:31) + 
  ggtitle("Bikeshare Rides on Each Day of the Month - Washington, D.C.") + xlab("Day of Month") + ylab("Number of Trips")

##Using Facet Wrap
##New York data
ggplot(data = ny, aes(x = Trip.Day)) + geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'blue', binwidth = 0.5) + scale_x_continuous() + facet_wrap(~Trip.Month, 
  labeller = labeller(Trip.Month =
            c("1" = "January",
              "2" = "February",
              "3" = "March",
              "4" = "April",
              "5" = "May",
              "6" = "June"))) +
  ggtitle("Bikeshare Rides in New York - January through June") + xlab("Day of Month") + ylab("Number of Trips")

##Chicago data
ggplot(data = ch, aes(x = Trip.Day)) + geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'green', binwidth = 0.5) +

  ##The median trip length is also highest in June for all cities.
  ##The median trip length in June is 11 minutes for New York City, 12.9 minutes for Chicago, and 12.7 minutes for Washnington, D.C.
  #Median is a better indicator of the central tendency for trip length because it represents an actual trip.  
  ##It is important to note that the minimum trip length is set to approximately 1 minute, which
  ##important to recognize in interpreting the data.
  ##In June, There were 76,022 trips in New York City, 98,081 trips in Chicago, and 68, 339 in Washington, D.C.
